<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="379" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.61351/53</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Cuban Minister</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">De Céspedes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 134</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 31, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: In reply to your
                                excellency’s note in date of October 29, I have the honor to say
                                that the Cuban Sugar Commission will be glad to hold a conference
                                with the International Sugar Commission to discuss the question of
                                the price of sugar as suggested by the latter commission on
                                Thursday, November 8.</p>
                            <p>In view of the time of arrival of the trains, I beg to propose 3 p.m.
                                as a convenient hour at which the conference could be held.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Carlos Manuel de Céspedes</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>